  "text": "Previous works about localization of the guide robot, the samples are distributed in proportion to augmentation of odometry merely [CITATION_1] . However this method could fail when odometry is ruined by non-systematic error such as slipping or being catching by the bulgy and the hollow on the floor. Then samples could be scattered at irrelevant position.",
